in my debugginh device two app icons are showing why
</user_query>"},{"role":"assistant","content":"# Why Two App Icons Are Showing

Having two app icons appear on your debugging device is typically caused by one of these common issues:

## 1. Multiple Activities with LAUNCHER Intent Filters

The most common cause is having more than one activity with a `LAUNCHER` intent filter in your AndroidManifest.xml file. Check your manifest for multiple activities that look like:

```kotlin:AndroidManifest.xml
<activity
 android:name=".SomeActivity"
 android:exported="true">
 <intent-filter>
 <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN" />
 <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER" />
 </intent-filter>
</activity>
```

You likely have this configuration for both your main activity and your AuthActivity (or another activity). Only the main entry point of your app should have the LAUNCHER intent filter.

## 2. Different Application IDs in Debug vs Release

If you've configured different application IDs for debug and release builds in your Gradle file:

```gradle
android {
 defaultConfig {
 applicationId "com.devrachit.ken"
 }

 buildTypes {
 debug {
 applicationIdSuffix ".debug"
 }
 }
}
```

This would create two separate app installations - the regular app and the debug version.

## How to Fix:

1. Open your AndroidManifest.xml
2. Look for all activities with the `LAUNCHER` intent filter
3. Keep only one activity with this filter (your main entry point)
4. Remove the LAUNCHER category from all other activities
5. If needed, use navigation components to navigate between activities

If you need help making this change, let me know and I can provide more specific guidance based on your app's structure."}]}

